cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on improving video quality in wireless networks through multipath transmission and path selection. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the paper specifically mentions video telephony service and improving video quality. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses bandwidth aggregation and congestion control algorithms. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the paper discusses deploying relay servers to form an overlay network. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses a congestion control algorithm and maintaining throughput stability and fairness.
